Honest Abe<//name>
<Rating>1</Rating><UserId.>112049589826237049377</UserId.>< review>
NOISE is a huge issue at the complex.

Current resident here, who's been living at JPT for over 1 year now. The main reason I renewed my lease this year - even though they raised the price - was bc I wanted to avoid having to move during the height of COVID-19 in CA (felt unsafe & unsanitary).

The apt is modern and aesthetically beautiful, but I can't emphasize enough how CHEAPLY made it is. That's probably why the NOISE issue is so prevalent here. I can hear my upstairs walking around in their unit, placing things down on their floor, talking loudly/arguing/yelling, and playing booming music that SHAKES (yes PHYSICALLY shakes) my unit. I've lived in apts throughout SoCal and in cities throughout the US, but this is the 1st time I've come across this type of issue at a "luxury" apartment at this price.

PREVIOUS ALLIANCE MANAGEMENT: NEGATIVE FIVE STARS - The previous Alliance Management made it their business to IGNORE noise complaints. As usual, upstairs was blasting their music (I understand if it was Friday night to blow off some steam and wind down, but from FRIDAY MORNING all the way into AFTERNOON). It was interfering with my ability work in the peace & quiet of my own home during regular business hours, so I called the office to file a noise complaint and see if they can help me resolve the situation officially. AUTUMN who picked up my call after 3-4 times of trying to reach the LEASING OFFICE's RESIDENT LINE was ANNOYED that I was calling with a noise complaint and said she would follow up with me after talking to my upstairs. It was almost end of the day (5pm-ish), the noise from upstairs was still the blasting, and I hadn't heard from her in the past 4 hours, so I called back - failing to reach them again. After another 4-5 attempts trying to reach the RESIDENT LINE, Autumn picked up, sounded annoyed, and transferred me to another office person MIKE who was dismissive of my noise complaint - telling me they don't have time for noise complaints because the office "Needs to handle files and stuff" and the upstairs sounds like "They're just having a party" (from the morning?), I can't speak to the leasing office manager because I "just missed her". Clearly, they have time and resources to "handle files", but not for ensuring a live-able environment for their CURRENT RESIDENTS. Beyond being unable to see through and document my noise complaint, what really FRUSTRATED me was their dismissive attitude, unresponsiveness, and unprofessionalism in dodging my calls because they didn't want to handle noise complaints.

CURRENT GREYSTAR MANAGEMENT: ONE STAR - I've had a better overall experience with the current management, which is why I am really DISAPPOINTED in the way that they're handling noise complaints. They've been more responsive and attentive to the office's RESIDENT LINE and handling our living/community issues, which was especially important and appreciated during QUARANTINE as everyone was staying home much, much longer than used to. Back in July, (I'm guessing because of the influx of noise complaints they were getting), the new management sent out an email communication to all the residents reminding us of noise etiquette (basically how to be good neighbors 101) and that they contracted an after office hours on-site Courtesy Patrol. I was really happy that the office was FINALLY addressing the noise complaints/issue professionally. HOWEVER, this October I contacted the Courtesy Patrol number to file a noise complaint. I was told by this 3rd party Courtesy Patrol that JPT is no longer using their services. I had received the notification from the leasing office about the Courtesy Patrol only 3 months prior. No email from the office that they stopped using Courtesy Patrol for handling noise complaints. EXTREMELY DISAPPOINTED in this management's handling of noise complaints as well....

One star is for the maintenance staff (John & his Team) who has been nothing but friendly & helpful with any maintenance problems I've had with the unit (and there have been alot because it's so poorly and cheaply built.)</review>

Please think carefully before you decide to move here.

Before we moved in, we have signed the welcome letter like five times. staff at leasing office kept making mistakes about the content. We moved here around a month ago. After a week living here, we noticed the leasing office gave us the wrong address. Because of that, we had to sign the lease again and it caused us lots of troubles. We had to call every business we placed an order online to change the shipping address.

We have been charged $50 vacant service fee and they gave us a gift card try to resolve the problem. The gift card is in a resident account and we don’t know how to use it. When I ask for further instruction, they don’t respond to that. Furthermore, we received the electricity bill for the wrong address and they told me they will deal with that but they didn’t. I received same bill request after a month. I have been double charged for activating the service from gas company for changing to the correct service address, and the leasing office refused to pay us back for the extra charge caused by their mistake.

When I asked the leasing office about setting the Wifi, they provided us a contact information Ray from at&t. That person was irresponsible. We told Ray to change the service address and he forgot to do that, so the Wifi couldn’t been set  up when the technician person arrived. It caused us huge inconvenience since it takes few days after reschedule the service installation. My housemate had been double charged from at&t and Ray said twice that he would solve the issue for her. <Rating>3< /Rating>< Review>
The staff is usually courteous and friendly. If you have a problem, contact the leasing office and let them know of your concerns, you just may need to give them a reminder or two.

This is supposed to be a smoke-free complex, but there are tenants who are too stubborn to abide by the rules and smoke anyway. More tenants need to speak up and say something about it because we pay to live in a smoke-free building. Sadly, management has been present while we spoke of a neighbor sitting on their porch, smoking. Every day, that same person was on their porch smoking which makes it appear that management doesn’t enforce the no smoking rule and the hallway always smells like weed.

The area is very upbeat and there’s lots to do just here at the complex itself. Whether you’re interested in social gatherings, rooftop views, or lounging at the pool, you’ll have plenty to do. Just be warned, this neighborhood is flooded with pet owners, so you may come across some rather large dogs here.<//Review>

Applied to these new and beautiful apartment homes earlier this month, my application was denied, this was okay as I wasn't sure if I would be approved initially anyway, I was very upfront with my situation, the thing that got me to apply when speaking with the leasing office was when the told me that if denied initially that I would be able to work with the screening company on getting approved, I thought great, some help pointing me in the direction of what I need to take care of, happily paid the 2 app fees for my wife and I, they also wanted a $250 holding deposit, we asked if we end up not renting from you how the holding deposit is refunded as we had recently had a terrible expirience with another company where it took near 3 months to get the refund, the leasing agent told us that the deposit would be returned to the same form of payment we use to make it, great! We paid the leasing deposit, our application came back declined and the leasing agent gave us a phone number to call for the screening company and again told us that they would help get us approved, after waiting on hold for about an hour we were informed all the screening company will do is provide a copy of the screening report and zero information as to why we were declined, I called back the apartments to ask some more questions as to what we can do to get approved, were there some debts we could pay off to get us approved? Would a cosigner help get us approved? I was told that a manager would call me back by the next day, 2 days later and still no call so I called with the same questions, again I was told they would have their manager take a look and get in touch with me that day, this time I did receive a call back as I was told, they let me know that paying off just the 1 most recent debt would not likely get me approved, at this point I decide to throw in the towel and cut my losses as that was not an answer to any of my questions, nor did they even slightly answer the question about a cosigner, I tell the lady that I was speaking to thank you for the information, how long approximately before we see our deposit hold return, to which she then asks me where I would like the check mailed to, I pause and take a deep breath because I see where this is going as it's exactly what I wanted to avoid doing again, I explain to her that we do not have a current mailing address because we have been using Airbnb for the last couple of months while trying to find our new home here in CA, our last mailing address is for Oregon and we haven't been there for 3 months that is why we asked about this process in the very beginning, she lets me know she will speak with her manager and give me a call back again. I get a call back and she lets me know that they will have the check mailed to their office, I ask how long this process will be and I am told just under a week, takes a couple of days to process and get in, I think that's not terrible, and thank her for her help, that brings us to today, it's been a little over a week, I call to check in with them thinking maybe things are a little slow because of the holiday we just had, no big deal, the person I speak with let's me know that nothing has arrived but it takes 21 days! Long story short the apartments are beautiful, if you can deal with the lies and misinformation from staff then this would be a great place, very frustrating when you go in open and honest and do not get the honesty in return, we had no issue with being declined, our past is ours and we own it, we fell in love with the home and we were willing to do whatever we needed to get in, whether paying off debts, paying a larger deposit, using a cosigner, but no one could tell us why we were declined so we have no idea what to fix and then topped off with the lies about our holding deposit, may very well be a blessing in disquise.</review>

< text>
Living here has been an absolute fantastic experience.
First, the staff is amazing. They've gone completely out of their way to help us out and always ask if we need anything. They're very friendly and professional and make you feel important.
Second, the community is very attractive. They have a cleaning crew EVERYDAY and focus on different areas of the community to keep everything looking nice. I'd recommend JPT to everyone who is looking for a great place to live.< /text>

<Review>Amazing ! I went there earlier right before noon. Their bagels and tea are for sure amazing! I can't wait to try more food on their menu~

I did sit outside to smoke hookah as well and the hookah is really good! I tried one of their mixes... I forgot EXACTLY what it is called but it has the word "Summer" in it- I recommend that mix. It was really good! I don't like hookah that's too sweet or anything so if you're like that as well, that was is nice and smooth.

Also, the person that served me was named Alex. He was awesome! He had amazing customer service! The other workers were good, too.

I do see myself going there often :)

<text>Went here by chance while doing some business in the area. Wow, this place has a very cozy, comfortable and relaxed atmosphere that is very inviting. You can sit at their sidewalk tables in a nice quiet location with an amazing view of the foothills. The menu is easy to read and has pictures for mostly all items. < review>
Even in LA, it is so hard to find places I can dine at. With my chronic health challenges, I’m avoiding a lot of harmful ingredients and H.O.P.E. is one of the only 3 restaurants I feel safe dinning at due to their substitution options. And substitution DOES NOT reduce flavor one bit! I get the Spicy Noodle and veggie soup.

Also to note, Postmates screwed multiple times tonight forcing the restaurant to deal with this inconvenience. The chef was so helpful, empathetic, and professional. I’m so happy that I can count on this place.<//review>

< text>
My favorite restaurant in the area! It’s great for vegans (which I am), but I take all my non-vegan family and friends here too and everyone loves it. The prices are fantastic for LA and it is quick to get in and out. It’s totally a hidden gem. My faves are the mac n’ cheese, the orange chicken, the curries and the new “fish” fillets. <UserId.>111217793845808378532<//UserId.>< name>
Rick Lupert< /name>
< Date>
1544482499824<//Date>
<rate>4<//rate><Text>H.O.P.E. kitchen is an all vegan thai food place with plenty of tasty meat substitute and gluten free options for every diet. Okay, full disclosure, H.O.P.E. stands for “Healthy Organic Positive Eating” which is just the other side of new-agey for my general comfort level so I was a little skeptical going on…but everything we had was delicious and we weren’t made to answer any “questions of the day” or required to order our food using words that indicate what mood we were in…so great start!

We started with the crispy chicken side-dish. This was as good as any fish and chips dish I remember having…the “chicken” was battered in a gluten free batter, and was tender on the inside. Although it was more like a fish dish as I said, it was super-super-delicious and I started to fantasize about adding a lemon squeeze and some properly cooked fries and, done!  This is crave-worthy

I had, from the House Special menu, the Kai Ga-Tiam & Sticky rice. This was okay, but the side of sticky rice it came with was not my favorite sticky rice ever (it was a little dry to be sticky), and the chicken was a bit over cooked and reminded me of vegetarian “beef” I’ve gotten elsewhere. The broccoli this came with was perfectly cooked, and the hot sauce it was served with was nice in moderation

My wife had the See-Ew (gluten free) which I tried a little of and we both thought it was among the best tasting “Pad See Ew” dishes we’d ever had. Again with perfectly cooked veggies.

Our kid who has more basic tastes got a Veggie Lovers with “beef” on the side. The beef was a little too crispy and dry, and he didn’t like it. He did order it on the side and we think it might have been better cooked with dish so it was moister.

They brought our side of brown rice on the side in the shape of a heart which made us feel the rice loved us. :)

Everyone was friendly including our server…and we liked that the menu, which we already knew was all vegan, had labeled each dish that was gluten free.

There’s plenty more to choose from here with an extensive soups, starters, noodles, curries and more sections of their menu…I’d come back based on crave-worthiness of the “Crispy Chicken” (Which I’ll forever think of as fish and chips) alone. (and they do have french fries to so I can roll my own!)<//Text>< pics>

I was immediately brought in, had my scan and was in and out within about 20 min without so much as a hiccup. Can’t say enough about the experience I had with this site. It was actually second time I’ve been here but many years ago and I don’t remember for what exactly but I do not recall anything negative backbthen either. There should be more people like Debbie.
